# Resend Documentation

Use current Resend docs — do not rely on training data for API details.

## Priority 1: Context7 MCP

Use Context7 `query-docs` with library ID `/resend/resend-node`.

Example queries:

- "send email react component Node.js"
- "Resend API key authentication error handling"
- "from to subject html text batch send"

Workflow: search with the user's specific sending task, then confirm API shape before implementing.

## Priority 2: Direct sources (shell fallback)

```bash
# Node SDK readme and API reference on GitHub
curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/resend/resend-node/canary/readme.md
curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/resend/resend-node/canary/_autodocs/api-reference/emails.md
```

Official docs: https://resend.com/docs

## Conventions in this repo

- Resend is used only in `apps/api` for magic-link auth emails.
- `RESEND_API_KEY` is a Worker secret (`.env` locally, dashboard in production).
- `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` is a Worker var (verified sender, e.g. `Costly <login@yourdomain.com>`).
- Send helpers live in `apps/api/src/emails/`; pass React Email components via the `react` field on `resend.emails.send`.
- In development (`NODE_ENV=development`), magic links are logged to the console — Resend is not called.

## Notes

- Resend has no official docs MCP in this repo; Context7 is the primary path.
- The `from` address must use a domain verified in the Resend dashboard.
- Use `react` prop on `emails.send` for React Email templates (Resend renders server-side).
